\sin x -\sqrt 3 \cos x=\sin x -\tan(\frac{\pi}{3}) \cos x=\sin x -\frac{\sin(\frac{\pi}{3})}{\cos(\frac{\pi}{3})} \cos x\\ =\frac{\sin x\cos(\frac{\pi}{3}) -\sin(\frac{\pi}{3})\cos x}{\cos(\frac{\pi}{3})} =\frac{\sin (x-\frac{\pi}{3})}{\cos(\frac{\pi}{3})} 
\sin(x)\pm A \cos(x)
